OKEY ‘Oakfil’ Ezugwu’s series, ‘Gifted’ has ranked second most loved drama series in 2021 on IROKOtv, closely behind audience favourite series, Blood of Enogie.. By audience demand, Oakfil has commenced season three of the hit drama series. Season one and two premiered in 2021 and received much critical acclaim and commendations for their originality. ‘Gifted’ features Ifeoma Obinwa, Somadina Adinma, Benjamine Touitou, Kenechukwu Eze, Jenifer Okoli, Chinonso Arubayi, Maryann Apollo, Stan Igboanugo, and fast-rising actress, Oge Gabriel.   My entire acting career has been in Nollywood, Amata     Five Nigerian female celebrities who went from fat to fit     Eight Nigerian celebrities with traditional titles   According to Oakfil, season three will feature new faces that include Florence Owanta, Adaeze Phillo, Debby Frankson, Caroline Okonkwo, and Paul Vicks. - Advertisement - Read Also: My entire acting career has been in Nollywood, Amata “We are overwhelmed with the reception of seasons one and two. Season three is filled with twists and an incredible plot that even the audience will find themselves dazzled,” the producer, Okey Ezugwu said. Gifted, an Oakfil production for IROKOtv and directed by Filmboy Adeyemi Morafa, is a Cinderella story of Ebele, a young orphan girl who is raised by her paternal uncle and his wife. They stopped her education to fund their children while she becomes their slave and serves them wholeheartedly. Her only support is her paternal grandmother but she too is unable to save Ebele from the wickedness of her uncle’s family. Ebele’s passion is sewing and this is a gift passed on from her late mother.